  "local_port": 50276,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which Pakistani universities are recognized by Australian immigration department?",
  "response": "The Australian Department of Home Affairs assesses educational qualifications from around the world, including those from Pakistan. While the department does not maintain a specific list of recognized universities, it generally recognizes degrees from universities that are accredited by the Higher Education Commission (HEC) of Pakistan.\n\nHere are some well-known Pakistani universities that are accredited by the HEC and are likely to be recognized by the Australian immigration authorities:\n\n1. **University of the Punjab, Lahore**\n2. **University of Karachi, Karachi**\n3. **National University of Sciences and Technology (NUST), Islamabad**\n4. **Quaid-i-Azam University, Islamabad**\n5. **Lahore University of Management Sciences (LUMS), Lahore**\n6. **Aga Khan University, Karachi**\n7. **University of Engineering and Technology (UET), Lahore**\n8. **Institute of Business Administration (IBA), Karachi**\n9. **COMSATS University Islamabad**\n10. **University of Peshawar, Peshawar**\n\nTo ensure that your specific qualification is recognized, it's advisable to:\n\n1. **Check HEC Accreditation:** Confirm that the university and the program you completed are accredited by the HEC.\n2. **Qualification Assessment:** Use the Australian Government's Country Education Profiles to understand how your qualification compares to the Australian education system.\n3. **Skills Assessment:** Depending on your occupation and visa subclass, you might need to have your skills assessed by the relevant Australian assessing authority.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's recommended to contact the Australian Department of Home Affairs or consult their official website.",
